Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[If it is _Molluscum contagiosum_, this virus usually infects children and is endemic worldwide. _M. contagiosum_ is a common benign skin disease that is caused by a poxvirus, classified as the single species in the genus _Molluscipoxvirus_ in the subfamily _Chordopoxvirinae_. _M. contagiosum_ virus has not been propagated in cultured cells, but restriction-fragment length analysis suggests that at least 4 strains exist. And if it were _M. contagiosum_ in these horses, we would probably have seen it before in other non-human hosts. Hopefully clarification is on its way.

For a map of Australia, go to http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/australia/australia_pol99.jpg. - Mod.MHJ

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/21Bk.]
